Reasoning: The paper discusses decoding schemes for the McEliece public-key cryptosystem based on moderate-density parity-check (MDPC) codes. This topic falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines, including information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), coding theory (cs.CC), systems and control (cs.SY), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Given the focus on decoding algorithms and error-correction performance, cs.IT and cs.CC are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses resilience against attacks, which suggests cs.CR as a likely sub-category. The use of message-passing algorithms and belief propagation further supports cs.SY and cs.DS as possible sub-categories.
